 <text>
  <front>
   <head>THE BEAU MONDE, OR THE Pleasures of St. JAMES'S. A BALLAD.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">! St.  is a lovely Place,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">'Tis better than the City;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For there are Balls and Operas,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And ev'ry Thing that's pretty.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There's little Lady</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And bouncing Dame</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Duce a Bit will either Sing</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Unless they're each a</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And when we've ek'd out History,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And made them Rival Queens,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">They'll warble sweetly on the Stage,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And scold behind the Scenes:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When having fill'd their Pockets full,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">No longer can they stay;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But turn their Backs upon the Town,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And scamper all away.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Belles and Beaux cry after them,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">With all their might and main;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And  is sent in haste</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">To fetch 'em back again.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then Hey! for a Subscription</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">To th' Opera, or the Ball;</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Silver Ticket walks about</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Untill there comes a Call.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">This puts them into doleful Dumps,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Who were both blith and Gay;</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There's nothing spoils Diversion more</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Than telling what's to pay.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There's  has made the  mad,</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Who labour all they can;</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To pull his Reputation down,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And maul the</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="9" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But Wit and he so close are link'd,</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">In vain is all this Pother;</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">They never can demolish one</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Without destroying 'tother.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="10" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And there's Miss  lugs</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Our Nobles by the Ears,</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Till PONDER WELL by far Exceeds</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">The Musick of the Spheres.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="11" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="41" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When lo! to show the Wisdom Great</l>
     <l n="42" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Of  famous Town,</l>
     <l n="43" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">We set her up above her self,</l>
     <l n="44" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And then we take her down.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="12" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="45" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, there's your Beaux, with powder'd Cloaths,</l>
     <l n="46" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Bedaub'd from Head to Shin;</l>
     <l n="47" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Their Pocket-holes adorn'd with Gold,</l>
     <l n="48" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">But not a souse within:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="13" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="49" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And there's your pretty Gentlemen,</l>
     <l n="50" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">All dress'd in Silk and Sattin;</l>
     <l n="51" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That get a Spice of ev'ry Thing,</l>
     <l n="52" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Excepting Sense and Latin.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="14" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="53" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And there's your Cits that have their Tits,</l>
     <l n="54" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">In  so sweet.</l>
     <l n="55" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But costlier Tits they keep, God wot!</l>
     <l n="56" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">In  and</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="15" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="57" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And there's your green Nobility,</l>
     <l n="58" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">On Citizens so witty,</l>
     <l n="59" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whose Fortune and Gentility,</l>
     <l n="60" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Arose from  City.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="16" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="61" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">We go to Bed when others rise,</l>
     <l n="62" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">And Dine at Candle-light;</l>
     <l n="63" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There's nothing mends Complexion more,</l>
     <l n="64" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Than turning Day to Night.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="17" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="65" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For what is Title, Wealth, or Wit,</l>
     <l n="66" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">If Folks are not Genteel?</l>
     <l n="67" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or how can they be said to live,</l>
     <l n="68" met="-+|-+|-+|-" line_length="7">Who know not what's</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
